reviews.review_text:
Being a Sunday the place was quite full, but we got seats immediately.
we reached late so no thali was available.
We ordered A La Carte...food was good.
Service was lousy, prawns curry was deliicious , so was sukha teesryo, prawns hakka noodles quantity  was quite less.our fried fish came after we finished our food.
Took 15 minutes to get water and for finger bowls.
Extremely bad service.

This is a nice place by the Panjim Miramar road with a lot of free inhouse parking services. The restaurant provides both AC and non AC sections. The ambience is good in AC as well as the breezy non-AC section. I preferred the cool natural breezy area. I tried the squid golden fry, chonaak rava fry which was fresh and crispy. Among the drinks, Cinderella was very sweet having only the taste of the slice.The gimlet was good but the quantity was very less.  One must try the chicken 65 at this place which has a good taste. Coriander chicken is nice and yummy, a must try here. The service is great here. The waiters are very polite and welcoming. Overall a good place to visit with family or friends.

•Trip type: Dinner with Friends

•Service: 3.0

•Location: 3.5

•Hotel highlights: Nice place suited for family & friends.

•Walkability: No walking distance; it's Just on the road with good enough inhouse free parking.

Went for Sunday lunch.
This "multi-cuisine " restaurant is more famous for its Goan cuisine, so suggest stick to that.
It has totally ~300 covers, 140 in ac section (most prefered), 40 in Alfresco, & 150 outdoors along Promenade.
Starters:
Prawn Dangar (cutlets) - most disappointing in both Presentation & taste - suggest pl Avoid!.
Butter garlic squids - good.
Entrée: "Kurylo" (crab) butter garlic - excellent in taste, & VFM @Rs 580.
Kingfish thali- v good.
Service was attentive.
Note: Indoors ac gets full by 1.15pm, so go early.
Would strongly recommend this place for good Goan cuisine, in a decent ambiance.
